headline: 4 S&P 500 Stocks Down 20% or More That You'll Regret Not Buying
summary: Many investors frantically read the news last week: The S&P 500 officially entered correction territory, which is a drop of at least 10%.  The market correction may be short-lived, but it turns out that there are plenty of high-quality S&P 500 stocks that are down 20% or more.  Included among the underperformers are Alphabet (NASDAQ: GOOG)(NASDAQ: GOOGL), Vistra (NYSE: VST), Dollar General (NYSE: DG), and Airbnb (NASDAQ: ABNB).

headline: Are Pop-Tarts on the Chopping Block With GOP Cuts?
summary: A weakening economy is already pressuring consumer spending, with shoppers cutting back on snacks and cigarettes.  Now, benefit reductions for low-income consumers could pile on still more pressure.  While tax cuts could put more money in the pockets of middle-class and wealthy families, Congress might pair them with reductions to programs including Medicaid and the Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP), also known as food stamps.

headline: 3 Reasons Why an S&P 500 Correction Won't Stop Me From Buying More Dollar General Stock
summary: Whereas the S&P 500 last hit an all-time high mere weeks ago, Dollar General stock hasn't sniffed an all-time high since late 2022.  A good percentage of this drop for Dollar General stock is entirely legitimate, in my view.  For Dollar General, this hasn't been a problem.
